                            <comment id="57194" author="pjones" created="Sat, 27 Apr 2013 20:57:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56118" author="doug" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2013 17:25:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I used the &quot;Add/Remove Software&quot; app on CentOS 6.3.  I installed three packages:&lt;br/&gt;
wireshark-1.2.15-2.el6_2.1&lt;br/&gt;
wireshark-devel-1.2.15-2.el6_2.1&lt;br/&gt;
wireshark-gnome-1.2.15-2.el6_2.1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As Nathaniel points out, this is too old a version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56016" author="adilger" created="Wed, 10 Apr 2013 16:42:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doug, is there a wireshark-devel package that you need to install for the headers?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56007" author="utopiabound" created="Wed, 10 Apr 2013 14:50:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Add version check to Makefile&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/6011&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/6011&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56002" author="utopiabound" created="Wed, 10 Apr 2013 13:26:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The default CentOS 6 wireshark (1.2.x is too old).  We need at least 1.6.8.  I can add a Makefile check I think.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
